President Joe Biden has proclaimed May 9, 2023, as National Teacher Appreciation Day and May 7 through May 13, 2023, as National Teacher Appreciation Week. In his proclamation, he emphasizes the dedication and hard work of teachers and early childhood educators who shape the lives of students. President Biden calls for better pay, improved working conditions, and increased recruitment and retention efforts for teachers. He highlights the investments made through the American Rescue Plan, which have resulted in the addition of over 500,000 educators and staff in public schools, as well as increased mental health services and afterschool programs. The President's Fiscal Year 2024 Budget calls for $600 billion to provide access to high-quality child care and preschool programs and higher wages for early childhood educators. Additionally, the budget aims to increase funding for Title I schools, raise salaries for Head Start staff, and address shortages of special education teachers. President Biden also mentions the Public Service Loan Forgiveness program, which has provided student loan forgiveness to over 450,000 public service employees, including teachers. He underscores the importance of keeping teachers and students safe by enacting gun safety laws and investing in student mental health. The proclamation concludes with a call to honor and support teachers through appropriate activities, events, and programs during National Teacher Appreciation Day and Week.